  "texts": [
    "GANs, VAEs, Flow-Based Models, and Diffusion Models have the following applications:• Generative adversarial networks (GAN) Applications: GANs are commonly used in picture creation, style transfer, and data enhancement.",
    "They excel at jobs that require the creation of realistic and highfidelity samples, such as photorealistic photos, art, and even deepfakes.",
    "• Variational autoencoders (VAEs)Applications: VAEs excel in applications requiring organized latent representations, such as image reconstruction, picture production with controlled properties, and feature learning.",
    "They are especially effective in situations when explicit control of the creative process is required.• Flow-based models Applications: Flow-based models, such as Real NVP, are useful in situations that require explicit density estimates and invertible mappings.",
    "They are frequently used in activities like uncertainty quantification and anomaly identification."
  ],
